frus:attachment.p:
As special subjects to be brought up at the conference were mentioned:

Treatment of submarines and airships;

Destruction of neutral prizes and the question of granting the
                                right of asylum to such prizes;

Questions arising out of the issuing and application of
                                “black-lists” by the belligerents;

Preparatory steps for adjusting the economic situation after the
                                war and of apprising each other of steps taken during the war for
                                economical-political purposes.
